article.headline: Mount St. Mary's, Md. 80, Wagner 70
article.story: EMMITSBURG, Md. (AP) -- Gus Durr scored a team-high 18 points and grabbed five rebounds, and Mount St. Mary's, Maryland, defeated Wagner 80-70 Thursday night. Kelly Beidler sparked a 9-0 run by the Mountaineers (7-13, 6-3 NEC) in the game's last 90 seconds with a steal and an assist. Beidler finished the game with seven points, four rebounds, two assists and two steals. Mychal Kearse contributed 17 points and a game-high eight rebounds. Mark Porter led Wagner (6-13, 3-5 NEC) with 18 points and five assists. James Ulrich recorded 17 points and Joey Mundweiler scored 10 points.
